<h1>Laser Graffiti Removal</h1>

<p>
PulseClean provides laser graffiti removal for commercial buildings,
heritage sites, transport infrastructure, and public spaces.
Laser cleaning removes paint, ink, and coatings without damaging
the underlying surface.
</p>

<h2>Why Laser Graffiti Removal</h2>

<p>
Traditional graffiti removal methods rely on chemicals, pressure washing,
or abrasive blasting. These approaches often damage surfaces or spread
contaminants into surrounding areas.
</p>

<p>
Laser cleaning uses controlled pulsed energy to break down paint layers,
allowing operators to remove graffiti with high precision while protecting
the original material.
</p>

<h2>Suitable Surfaces</h2>

<ul>
<li>Sandstone and heritage stone</li>
<li>Concrete and masonry</li>
<li>Brick surfaces</li>
<li>Metal panels</li>
<li>Transport infrastructure</li>
<li>Public art and monuments</li>
</ul>

